        "summary": "In tennis, top seed Italy&#8217;s Jannik Sinner retained the Wimbledon men&#8217;s singles title, defeating second seed Germany&#8217;s Alexander Zverev 6-7(7), 7-6(2), 6-3, 6-4 in the final at the All England Club last night. It is Sinner&#8217;s second consecutive Wimbledon men&#8217;s singles title and his fifth Grand Slam singles title. He also became the 10th player […]",
        "article": "In tennis, top seed Italy&#8217;s Jannik Sinner retained the Wimbledon men&#8217;s singles title, defeating second seed Germany&#8217;s Alexander Zverev 6-7(7), 7-6(2), 6-3, 6-4 in the final at the All England Club last night. It is Sinner&#8217;s second consecutive Wimbledon men&#8217;s singles title and his fifth Grand Slam singles title. He also became the 10th player to successfully defend the Wimbledon men&#8217;s singles crown. In the women&#8217;s doubles final, the 10th-seeded Chinese-French pair of Guo Hanyu and Kristina Mladenovic defeated the second-seeded Canadian-Brazilian duo of Gabriela Dabrowski and Luisa Stefani 6-3, 7-5 at Centre Court in London last evening to win the title.",
